The White House has strongly condemned the Government of Iran's intentions to execute Ms. Sakineh Mohammadi Ashtiani. They criticize the lack of transparency and due process in her case, as well as the actions taken against her lawyer and family. The White House believes that this case highlights Iran's disregard for human rights, particularly those of women. They are calling on the Iranian government to halt the execution and ensure that Ashtiani receives the fair treatment and due process she deserves.